 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utheodwynriddermark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheodwynRiddermark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/2/02 2:35:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=29>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Alexandra of Anam Kara</span><hr size=1> I think Alexandra got slammed a bit hard on the first page, and I'd like to point out a couple of things.<br>
<br>
I spoke to Alexandra.  I wear several hats, one of them is frontperson ambassador of goodwill.<br>
<br>
Alexandra was tired, slightly bitter, she absolutely did not mean ill.  Whether I like it or not, whether I think it's nice or not, she was doing what she understood to be fair game on the RF mob.  From what I understand, she had camped RF earlier in the week, her camp was not respected (which in the eyes of VI is fair game as an FFA mob).<br>
<br>
She did not mean ill, did not believe that her being there and attempting to muster a force faster classified as KS.  I may not agree with her, but she in fairness was doing what she understood was right and proper in the situation.<br>
<br>
She said to me &quot;I have no disrespect for you and your guild, and I do wish you luck.  But I will try to get my people here faster than you, in order to get my epic that I am entitled to as much as anyone else.&quot;<br>
<br>
She was tired, she was cranky, but she was honest and straightforward about it and Alexandra was absolutely not trying any funny business.  She said what she was doing, conversed intelligently, and stuck to her guns.  I may not like it, but I have to respect it.<br>
<br>
EverQuest as a game is designed to reward the one who plays the most.  Camping for Ragefires, Rasters, Phinnys and such clearly proves this.  If we know that, perhaps we can arrive at some equitable and agreed-upon system.<br>
<br>
Or we can just kick each other in the teeth, say &quot;suck it up, whiner&quot; and play the game by those rules.  It's viable.  There's nothing illegal or underhanded about it.  But it would sadden the heck out of me to lower myself to that.<br>
<br>
Theo<br>
